Woman walked on to New York City's Kosciuszko Bridge from the Brooklyn side on Monday just before noon . 
  She climbed over the railing and stood on a section of metal piping 125 feet above Newtown Creek  . 
  Police spent more than two hours talking to her and eventually she agreed to be rescued . 
  A witness said she is a 44-year-old Polish mother-of-one going through a divorce with her husband . 
  She was rescued 'so she could be with her daughter'